<item>
            <title>[FLINK-2873] WebRuntimeMonitor does not start when multiple log files are present</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-2873</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;WebRuntimeMonitor&lt;/tt&gt; checks that in the given log directory only a single file following the pattern &lt;tt&gt;.&lt;b&gt;jobmanager&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;^\.&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;\.log&lt;/tt&gt; is present. If this is not the case, then the &lt;tt&gt;WebRuntimeMonitor&lt;/tt&gt; will fail to start. This is a problem if you have multiple &lt;tt&gt;JobManager&lt;/tt&gt; started which all log to the same directory as in the HA case, for example.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12906169">FLINK-2873</key>
