                            <comment id="14965247" author="githubbot" created="Tue, 20 Oct 2015 15:15:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user mxm opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/1271&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/1271&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-2873&quot; title=&quot;WebRuntimeMonitor does not start when multiple log files are present&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-2873&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-2873&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; detect &amp;amp; serve the job manager log files correctly&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    When multiple job masters are started or old log files are present, the&lt;br/&gt;
    log file could not be served through the web frontend.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    This commit determines the log file path through the &quot;log.dir&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
    environment variable or the config entry JOB_MANAGER_WEB_LOG_PATH_KEY.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    The latter is merely a shortcut for the unit tests or if multiple web&lt;br/&gt;
    frontends run inside one VM.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can merge this pull request into a Git repository by running:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    $ git pull &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/mxm/flink&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/mxm/flink&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-2873&quot; title=&quot;WebRuntimeMonitor does not start when multiple log files are present&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-2873&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-2873&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Alternatively you can review and apply these changes as the patch at:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/1271.patch&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/1271.patch&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To close this pull request, make a commit to your master/trunk branch&lt;br/&gt;
with (at least) the following in the commit message:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    This closes #1271&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;commit 32b723df432eb75b06f979c2a3aa387d31894da5&lt;br/&gt;
Author: Maximilian Michels &amp;lt;mxm@apache.org&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Date:   2015-10-20T15:07:40Z&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-2873&quot; title=&quot;WebRuntimeMonitor does not start when multiple log files are present&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-2873&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-2873&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; detect &amp;amp; serve the job manager log files correctly&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    When multiple job masters are started or old log files are present, the&lt;br/&gt;
    log file could not be served through the web frontend.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    This commit determines the log file path through the &quot;log.dir&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
    environment variable or the config entry JOB_MANAGER_WEB_LOG_PATH_KEY.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    The latter is merely a shortcut for the unit tests or if multiple web&lt;br/&gt;
    frontends run inside one VM.&lt;/p&gt;

